        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. The production volume is based on the production volume of clay roof tiles in Europe (RER dataset) and the nominal GDP 2016 of the World and the European Union. The nominal (current) GDP of the EU in 2016 was 1.39E+13 US$ and global was 7.65E+13 US$.
Sources: 
[1] Value of production quantity (m3) is retrieved from EuroStat for the year 2016, accessed on 20231010. Production quantity is 60'377'265 m3.
"Non-refractory clay building bricks (excluding of siliceous fossil meals or earths)", EUROPEAN UNION (28), PRODQNT in m3.
Industry, trade and services&gt;Statistics on the production of manufactured foods (prom)&gt;Sold production, exports and imports (ds-056120). Retrieved from: https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/databrowser/view/DS-056120__custom_7772056/default/table?lang=en
[2] ecoinvent v2 Report 7, Buildings, Part IV, p. 9. Average bulk brick density: 1.6 kg/dm3.
[3] https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/NY.GDP.MKTP.CD</productionVolumeComment>
